    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "StopSpeech",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " functionimmediately terminates speech on the channel specified by the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "chan",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter.After returning from ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "StopSpeech",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ",your application can safely release any text buffer that the speechsynthesizer has been using. You can call ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "StopSpeech",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " foran already idle channel without ill effect.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can also stop speech by passing a zero-length string (or,in C, a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "null",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " pointer)to one of the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpeakString",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpeakText",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ",or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpeakBuffer",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " functions.Doing this stops speech only in the specified speech channel (or,in the case of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpeakString",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ",in the speech channel managed internally by the Speech SynthesisManager).",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Before calling the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "StopSpeech",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function,you can use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpeechBusy",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function,which is described in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/applicationservices/1464581-speechbusy",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ",to determine if a synthesizer is still speaking. If you are working withmultiple speech channels, you can use the status selector with thefunction ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GetSpeechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " whichis described in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/applicationservices/1552220-getspeechinfo",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ",to determine if a specific channel is still speaking. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
